{
  "id": "001.4",
  "title": "Present Simple – Review",
  "topic": "Present Simple",
  "subtopic": "Review",
  "description": "Mixed practice with positive, negative, and question forms in the Present Simple",
  "lessons": [
    {
      "id": "001.4-lesson-1",
      "title": "Quick Review of the Present Simple",
      "content": "Use the Present Simple for routines, facts, habits, and stative verbs.\n\n| Form | Structure | Example |\n|------|-----------|---------|\n| Positive | Subject + Verb | She works hard. |\n| Negative | Subject + do/does not + Base Verb | She does not work on Sundays. |\n| Yes/No Question | Do/Does + Subject + Base Verb + ? | Does she work here? |\n| WH Question | Question word + do/does + Subject + Base Verb + ? | Where does she work? |\n\n📌 Remember: **he / she / it** takes **-s** in positive sentences, but after **does/doesn't** the main verb goes back to the **base form**."
    },
    {
      "id": "001.4-lesson-2",
      "title": "Final Check Before You Answer",
      "content": "Before answering, quickly check these points:\n\n• In positive sentences, does **he / she / it** need **-s / -es / -ies**?\n• In negative sentences, did you choose **don't** or **doesn't** correctly?\n• In questions, did you use **do/does** and keep the verb in the base form?\n• Did you choose the right question word: **what, when, where, why, how, how many**?\n\n⚠️ Common mistakes:\n• **She doesn't lives here.** -> **She doesn't live here.**\n• **Does he wants cake?** -> **Does he want cake?**\n• **What you want to do?** -> **What do you want to do?**"
    }
  ],
